data.title: Ray Dempsey confirms Limerick football management team
data.meta_description: New Limerick senior football manager Ray Dempsey has confirmed his backroom team for the upcoming season.
data.text:
New Limerick senior football manager Ray Dempsey has confirmed his backroom team for the upcoming season.

Former two time All Ireland winning Kerry footballer Anthony Maher has been confirmed as one of Dempsey's coaching team.

Also in the coaching team is Limerick's Eoin Joy who lined previously out against Maher at intercounty level.

While Kerry's Mark Fitzgerald rounds off the three man coaching team having been involved in the Kerry minor football setup last season.

Kildimo Pallaskenry stalwart John Chawke comes in as goalkeeping coach while Dempsey's fellow county man Martin Barrett as well as Feohanagh Castlemahon club man Michael Downey are selectors.

Manager

Ray Dempsey (Mayo)

Coaches

Anthony Maher (Kerry)

Eoin Joy (Fr. Casey's)

Mark Fitzgerald (Kerry)

Goalkeeping Coach/Selector

John Chawke (Kildimo/Pallaskenry)

Selector/Coach

Martin Barrett (Mayo)
